9.16. This past year has been difficult. I lost one of my closest friends, my grandmother, an aunt and an uncle. In a year where very little made sense, I’m grateful for those who made space for my pain and created moments of joy. Your kindness, consistency, and support anchored me. Thank you, God, for holding me gently through the turbulence. 

Last year, I uncovered new depths of perseverance, and I’m hopeful for an abundance of all the good things in the year ahead. Salud.
